    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36205 implements `:help!` which does a DWIM \"guess\" of the tag at cursor. But `:help {subject}` could also be more generous in the input it accepts.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- `:help {subject}` should accept \"sloppy\" `{subject}` and try to find a best-guess tag.\n    - Caveat: `:help {subject}` doesn't know the \"cursor position\" within `{subject}`, unlike `:help!`.\n\nNote that this would benefit from `:nospecial` https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/37862 and/or an improved `nvim_cmd(..., {magic={false})`.\n\n`nvim_cmd('help, {magic=false})` [currently fails](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/37862#issuecomment-4045936178) for some inputs:\n\n    :lua vim.cmd.help({ '=\"%foo|bar#baz\"', magic = { file = false, bar = false } })\n    E5108: Lua: [string \":lua\"]:1: Vim:E149: Sorry, no help for =\"%foo",
